<br>
Its really really fun and it feels awesome to break a zone that once used to kill hundreds hehe.  I remember one particularly nasty attempted break on Eci there were over 450 bodies in the zone according to the GM that showed mercy and depopped the zone.  <br>
<br>
This method means/is:<br>
<br>
-Probably unlike anything you've ever seen or done before<br>
-Is not the most efficient way to break Fear.  The best way to break fear is to just rush in and overpower the zone.<br>
-However its the safest way to break the zone as it has NEVER failed.<br>
-If you rush the zone and fail you can always fall back to this method to bail yourselves out.<br>
-Also doubles as an amazing CR technique.  With a necro You can CR a body from anywhere in the zone with a full repop.  Someone died in the center of the temple of fire or at CTs feet?  No problem.  I was able to save this guy's body that was 6 days old from poofing and neither of us died once during the CR that took about 10 minutes without corpse summon.<br>
<br>
Fear will always hold a special place for me because at one time it was a zone that I absolutely dreaded.  Several times I died in Fear and wondered if I would ever get my body back again or not.  Fear was brutally hard for the inexperienced especially prekunark.  Post kunark it wasn't that bad because you were higher level and you could ask the resident big dogs to come save you if you failed.  However back when I was trying Fear for the first time I was one of the big dogs and there was no one else that could come save us.   <p>----------------------- <BR>
